Steps to Deploy and Maintain
Setup Environment:
Populate .env with your credentials and paths.

Ensure SSL certificates are in place.

Install Dependencies:
Run npm install.

Test Locally:
Run npm run dev for development with nodemon.

Run npm test to execute tests.

Deploy:
Use ./deploy.sh to deploy with Docker Compose.

Configure Nginx if using a reverse proxy.

Monitor and Maintain:
Set up the cron job for monitor.sh.

Regularly check error.log and update dependencies (npm update).

Scaling Considerations:
Use a load balancer (e.g., Nginx) for multiple instances.

Configure MongoDB replica sets for high availability.

Monitor IPFS node performance and consider a dedicated IPFS cluster.

